# 📘 WHILE Loop

## Syntax

```text
START

SET i = 1

WHILE i <= Limit

    OUTPUT i

    SET i = i + 1

END WHILE

STOP
```

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

# 📘 Example

Print numbers from **1 to 5**

```text
START

SET i = 1

WHILE i <= 5

    OUTPUT i

    SET i = i + 1

END WHILE

STOP
```

Output

```text
1
2
3
4
5
```

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

# 📘 FOR vs WHILE

| FOR Loop | WHILE Loop |
|-----------|------------|
| Number of iterations is known | Number of iterations is unknown |
| Easier for counting | Easier for condition-based repetition |
| Initialization, condition and update are controlled by the loop | Initialization and update are written separately |

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

# 💻 Java vs Pseudocode

## FOR Loop

### Pseudocode

```text
FOR i = 1 TO 5

    OUTPUT i

END FOR
```

### Java

```java
for(int i = 1; i <= 5; i++){

    System.out.println(i);

}
```

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

## WHILE Loop

### Pseudocode

```text
SET i = 1

WHILE i <= 5

    OUTPUT i

    SET i = i + 1

END WHILE
```

### Java

```java
int i = 1;

while(i <= 5){

    System.out.println(i);

    i++;

}
```

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

# 📘 Even Numbers using FOR Loop

### Method 1 (Using IF)

```text
START

FOR i = 2 TO 10

    IF i % 2 == 0

        OUTPUT i

    END IF

END FOR

STOP
```

Output

```text
2
4
6
8
10
```

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

### Method 2 (Better Method)

```text
START

FOR i = 2 TO 10 STEP 2

    OUTPUT i

END FOR

STOP
```

Output

```text
2
4
6
8
10
```

⭐ **Interview Tip:** This method is more efficient because it skips odd numbers directly.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

